  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Moving your arm faster than lightning you punch a creature with more force than even the bijuu possess. Make a melee taijutsu attack dealing your unarmed damage +10d8. On a hit, the target creature takes must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save the target creature is knocked back 1 mile. If they strike a solid surface that's less than 5 feet thick, they tear through it, taking 6d6 bludgeoning damage for each surface they go through. If they strike a solid surface that's more than 5 feet thick, their movement stops and they take 6d6 bludgeoning damage. it, taking 6d6 bludgeoning damage. If the creature would be fully stopped before they have been knocked back half a mile they instead take 10d6 bludgeoning damage for the final instance of damage.</p>",
